{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6b1a048-690b-4fbf-bd33-642de2f67eb7","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n2. **Add the MSBuild property** (in your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio` as the test host adapter.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- Your existing `xunit` 2.9.3 package stays the same — no changes to test code needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8dcb3f4-ad14-4b05-beb1-99554a0235c5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":368,"requestId":"BC2B:2BEA6E:1C67F3D:1F707B8:69FA8F6E"},"id":"8fab3ad5-7013-49f2-a558-963712f12324","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:47.568Z","parentId":"00390553-68bc-425d-aaa9-50382d9158cb"}
